### Erroneous Code Reference (for debugging)
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String variable;
        System.out.println(variable);
    }
}
```

**Errors in the erroneous code:**
1. `variable` is declared but not initialized.
2. `System.out.println(variable)` will throw a `NullPointerException` because the variable is not assigned a value.

**Corrected version:**
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String variable = "Hello world";
        System.out.println(variable);
    }
}
```

---

All classes use the same variable `variable` and perform the required operations. No commas are used in the code.
